 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Basset was born in 1170 as the son of John Basset and Melisende. He married Cecilia de Dunstanville in 1200. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1170–":"1170–Surnud","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1175–1208":"1175–1208","1208–1262":"1208–1262","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1200":"1200","26 February 1208":"26. veebruar 1208","1175":"1175","1262":"1262","1140":"1140","1194":"1194","before 1208":"enne 1208","1170":"1170","1208":"1208"},"fi":{"1170–":"1170–Kuollut","1170–Male":"1170–Kuollut","1175–1208":"1175–1208","1208–1262":"1208–1262","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1200":"1200","26 February 1208":"26. helmikuuta 1208","1175":"1175","1262":"1262","1140":"1140","1194":"1194","before 1208":"ennen vuotta 1208","1170":"1170","1208":"1208"},"fr":{"1170–":"1170–Décédé","1170–Male":"1170–Décédé","1175–1208":"1175–1208","1208–1262":"1208–1262","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1200":"1200","26 February 1208":"26 février 1208","1175":"1175","1262":"1262","1140":"1140","1194":"1194","before 1208":"avant 1208","1170":"1170","1208":"1208","lifeSummary":"William Basset est né en 1170, fils de John Basset et Melisende. Il a épousé Cecilia de Dunstanville en 1200. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"1170–":"1170–Verstorben","1170–Male":"1170–Verstorben","11